{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":5000,"text":"Thank you very much, Chris. Everybody who came up here"},{"time":8000,"text":"said they were scared. I don't know if I'm scared,"},{"time":12000,"text":"but this is my first time of addressing an audience like this."},{"time":16000,"text":"And I don't have any smart technology for you to look at."},{"time":20000,"text":"There are no slides, so you'll just have to be content with me."},{"time":23000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26000,"text":"What I want to do this morning is share with you a couple of stories"},{"time":32000,"text":"and talk about a different Africa."},{"time":35000,"text":"Already this morning there were some allusions to the Africa"},{"time":39000,"text":"that you hear about all the time: the Africa of HIV/AIDS,"},{"time":44000,"text":"the Africa of malaria, the Africa of poverty, the Africa of conflict,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and the Africa of disasters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"While it is true that those things are going on,"},{"time":57000,"text":"there's an Africa that you don't hear about very much."},{"time":61000,"text":"And sometimes I'm puzzled, and I ask myself why."},{"time":65000,"text":"This is the Africa that is changing, that Chris alluded to."},{"time":69000,"text":"This is the Africa of opportunity."},{"time":71000,"text":"This is the Africa where people want to take charge of"},{"time":74000,"text":"their own futures and their own destinies."},{"time":76000,"text":"And this is the Africa where people are looking for partnerships"},{"time":79000,"text":"to do this. That's what I want to talk about today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"And I want to start by telling you"},{"time":85000,"text":"a story about that change in Africa."},{"time":88000,"text":"On 15th of September 2005, Mr. Diepreye Alamieyeseigha,"},{"time":93000,"text":"a governor of one of the oil-rich states of Nigeria,"},{"time":97000,"text":"was arrested by the London Metropolitan Police on a visit to London."},{"time":104000,"text":"He was arrested because there were transfers of eight million dollars"},{"time":109000,"text":"that went into some dormant accounts"},{"time":112000,"text":"that belonged to him and his family."},{"time":116000,"text":"This arrest occurred because there was cooperation"},{"time":118000,"text":"between the London Metropolitan Police"},{"time":121000,"text":"and the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission of Nigeria --"},{"time":124000,"text":"led by one of our most able and courageous people: Mr. Nuhu Ribadu."},{"time":131000,"text":"Alamieyeseigha was arraigned in London."},{"time":134000,"text":"Due to some slip-ups, he managed to escape dressed as a woman"},{"time":138000,"text":"and ran from London back to Nigeria where,"},{"time":141000,"text":"according to our constitution, those in office"},{"time":145000,"text":"as governors, president -- as in many countries --"},{"time":147000,"text":"have immunity and cannot be prosecuted. But what happened:"},{"time":152000,"text":"people were so outraged by this behavior that it was possible"},{"time":156000,"text":"for his state legislature to impeach him and get him out of office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"Today, Alams -- as we call him for short -- is in jail."},{"time":166000,"text":"This is a story about the fact that people in Africa"},{"time":171000,"text":"are no longer willing to tolerate corruption from their leaders."},{"time":177000,"text":"This is a story about the fact that people want their resources"},{"time":182000,"text":"managed properly for their good, and not taken out to places"},{"time":187000,"text":"where they'll benefit just a few of the elite."},{"time":190000,"text":"And therefore, when you hear about the corrupt Africa --"},{"time":194000,"text":"corruption all the time -- I want you to know that the people"},{"time":198000,"text":"and the governments are trying hard to fight this"},{"time":201000,"text":"in some of the countries, and that some successes are emerging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"Does it mean the problem is over? The answer is no."},{"time":208000,"text":"There's still a long way to go, but that there's a will there."},{"time":212000,"text":"And that successes are being chalked up on this very important fight."},{"time":216000,"text":"So when you hear about corruption,"},{"time":218000,"text":"don't just feel that nothing is being done about this --"},{"time":221000,"text":"that you can't operate in any African country"},{"time":224000,"text":"because of the overwhelming corruption. That is not the case."},{"time":227000,"text":"There's a will to fight, and in many countries, that fight is ongoing"},{"time":233000,"text":"and is being won. In others, like mine,"},{"time":237000,"text":"where there has been a long history of dictatorship in Nigeria,"},{"time":240000,"text":"the fight is ongoing and we have a long way to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"But the truth of the matter is that this is going on."},{"time":249000,"text":"The results are showing:"},{"time":251000,"text":"independent monitoring by the World Bank and other organizations"},{"time":255000,"text":"show that in many instances the trend is downwards"},{"time":259000,"text":"in terms of corruption, and governance is improving."},{"time":262000,"text":"A study by the Economic Commission for Africa showed"},{"time":266000,"text":"a clear trend upwards in governance in 28 African countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"And let me say just one more thing"},{"time":272000,"text":"before I leave this area of governance."},{"time":274000,"text":"That is that people talk about corruption, corruption."},{"time":277000,"text":"All the time when they talk about it"},{"time":279000,"text":"you immediately think about Africa."},{"time":281000,"text":"That's the image: African countries. But let me say this:"},{"time":285000,"text":"if Alams was able to export eight million dollars into an account in London --"},{"time":293000,"text":"if the other people who had taken money, estimated at"},{"time":297000,"text":"20 to 40 billion now of developing countries' monies"},{"time":301000,"text":"sitting abroad in the developed countries -- if they're able to do this,"},{"time":304000,"text":"what is that? Is that not corruption?"},{"time":308000,"text":"In this country, if you receive stolen goods, are you not prosecuted?"},{"time":313000,"text":"So when we talk about this kind of corruption, let us also think"},{"time":316000,"text":"about what is happening on the other side of the globe --"},{"time":319000,"text":"where the money's going and what can be done to stop it."},{"time":323000,"text":"I'm working on an initiative now, along with the World Bank,"},{"time":326000,"text":"on asset recovery, trying to do what we can"},{"time":329000,"text":"to get the monies that have been taken abroad --"},{"time":332000,"text":"developing countries' moneys -- to get that sent back."},{"time":335000,"text":"Because if we can get the 20 billion dollars sitting out there back,"},{"time":338000,"text":"it may be far more for some of these countries"},{"time":341000,"text":"than all the aid that is being put together."},{"time":344000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"The second thing I want to talk about is the will for reform."},{"time":355000,"text":"Africans, after -- they're tired, we're tired"},{"time":359000,"text":"of being the subject of everybody's charity and care."},{"time":364000,"text":"We are grateful, but we know that"},{"time":368000,"text":"we can take charge of our own destinies if we have the will to reform."},{"time":373000,"text":"And what is happening in many African countries now is a realization"},{"time":377000,"text":"that no one can do it but us. We have to do it."},{"time":381000,"text":"We can invite partners who can support us, but we have to start."},{"time":385000,"text":"We have to reform our economies, change our leadership,"},{"time":388000,"text":"become more democratic, be more open to change and to information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"And this is what we started to do"},{"time":396000,"text":"in one of the largest countries on the continent, Nigeria."},{"time":399000,"text":"In fact, if you're not in Nigeria, you're not in Africa."},{"time":402000,"text":"I want to tell you that."},{"time":403000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":404000,"text":"One in four sub-Saharan Africans is Nigerian,"},{"time":408000,"text":"and it has 140 million dynamic people -- chaotic people --"},{"time":414000,"text":"but very interesting people. You'll never be bored."},{"time":418000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"What we started to do was to realize"},{"time":421000,"text":"that we had to take charge and reform ourselves."},{"time":424000,"text":"And with the support of a leader"},{"time":426000,"text":"who was willing, at the time, to do the reforms,"},{"time":429000,"text":"we put forward a comprehensive reform program,"},{"time":431000,"text":"which we developed ourselves."},{"time":433000,"text":"Not the International Monetary Fund. Not the World Bank,"},{"time":436000,"text":"where I worked for 21 years and rose to be a vice president."},{"time":440000,"text":"No one can do it for you. You have to do it for yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"We put together a program that would, one: get the state"},{"time":446000,"text":"out of businesses it had nothing -- it had no business being in."},{"time":450000,"text":"The state should not be in the business"},{"time":452000,"text":"of producing goods and services"},{"time":453000,"text":"because it's inefficient and incompetent."},{"time":456000,"text":"So we decided to privatize many of our enterprises."},{"time":460000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":465000,"text":"We -- as a result, we decided to liberalize many of our markets."},{"time":469000,"text":"Can you believe that prior to this reform --"},{"time":472000,"text":"which started at the end of 2003, when I left Washington"},{"time":476000,"text":"to go and take up the post of Finance Minister --"},{"time":480000,"text":"we had a telecommunications company that was only able to develop"},{"time":484000,"text":"4,500 landlines in its entire 30-year history?"},{"time":489000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"Having a telephone in my country was a huge luxury."},{"time":494000,"text":"You couldn't get it. You had to bribe."},{"time":496000,"text":"You had to do everything to get your phone."},{"time":498000,"text":"When President Obasanjo supported and launched"},{"time":501000,"text":"the liberalization of the telecommunications sector,"},{"time":506000,"text":"we went from 4,500 landlines to 32 million GSM lines, and counting."},{"time":514000,"text":"Nigeria's telecoms market is the second-fastest growing in the world,"},{"time":519000,"text":"after China. We are getting investments of about a billion dollars a year"},{"time":524000,"text":"in telecoms. And nobody knows, except a few smart people."},{"time":530000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"The smartest one, first to come in,"},{"time":537000,"text":"was the MTN company of South Africa."},{"time":539000,"text":"And in the three years that I was Finance Minister,"},{"time":543000,"text":"they made an average of 360 million dollars profit per year."},{"time":548000,"text":"360 million in a market -- in a country that is a poor country,"},{"time":554000,"text":"with an average per capita income just under 500 dollars per capita."},{"time":559000,"text":"So the market is there."},{"time":561000,"text":"When they kept this under wraps, but soon others got to know."},{"time":565000,"text":"Nigerians themselves began to develop"},{"time":568000,"text":"some wireless telecommunications companies,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and three or four others have come in."},{"time":572000,"text":"But there's a huge market out there,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and people don't know about it, or they don't want to know."},{"time":580000,"text":"So privatization is one of the things we've done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"The other thing we've also done is to manage our finances better."},{"time":590000,"text":"Because nobody's going to help you and support you"},{"time":593000,"text":"if you're not managing your own finances well."},{"time":596000,"text":"And Nigeria, with the oil sector, had the reputation"},{"time":600000,"text":"of being corrupt and not managing its own public finances well."},{"time":605000,"text":"So what did we try to do? We introduced a fiscal rule"},{"time":610000,"text":"that de-linked our budget from the oil price."},{"time":612000,"text":"Before we used to just budget on whatever oil we bring in,"},{"time":616000,"text":"because oil is the biggest, most revenue-earning sector"},{"time":621000,"text":"in the economy: 70 percent of our revenues come from oil."},{"time":624000,"text":"We de-linked that, and once we did it, we began to budget"},{"time":628000,"text":"at a price slightly lower than the oil price"},{"time":631000,"text":"and save whatever was above that price."},{"time":636000,"text":"We didn't know we could pull it off; it was very controversial."},{"time":639000,"text":"But what it immediately did was that the volatility"},{"time":642000,"text":"that had been present in terms of our economic development --"},{"time":645000,"text":"where, even if oil prices were high, we would grow very fast."},{"time":649000,"text":"When they crashed, we crashed."},{"time":651000,"text":"And we could hardly even pay anything, any salaries, in the economy."},{"time":656000,"text":"That smoothened out. We were able to save, just before I left,"},{"time":660000,"text":"27 billion dollars. Whereas -- and this went to our reserves --"},{"time":666000,"text":"when I arrived in 2003, we had seven billion dollars in reserves."},{"time":671000,"text":"By the time I left, we had gone up to almost 30 billion dollars. And"},{"time":674000,"text":"as we speak now, we have about 40 billion dollars in reserves"},{"time":678000,"text":"due to proper management of our finances."},{"time":683000,"text":"And that shores up our economy, makes it stable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"Our exchange rate that used to fluctuate all the time"},{"time":689000,"text":"is now fairly stable and being managed so that business people"},{"time":693000,"text":"have a predictability of prices in the economy."},{"time":700000,"text":"We brought inflation down from 28 percent to about 11 percent."},{"time":706000,"text":"And we had GDP grow from an average of 2.3 percent the previous decade"},{"time":712000,"text":"to about 6.5 percent now."},{"time":716000,"text":"So all the changes and reforms we were able to make"},{"time":719000,"text":"have shown up in results that are measurable in the economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722000,"text":"And what is more important, because we want to get away from oil"},{"time":726000,"text":"and diversify -- and there are so many opportunities"},{"time":728000,"text":"in this one big country, as in many countries in Africa --"},{"time":733000,"text":"what was remarkable is that much of this growth came"},{"time":736000,"text":"not from the oil sector alone, but from non-oil."},{"time":739000,"text":"Agriculture grew at better than eight percent."},{"time":742000,"text":"As telecoms sector grew, housing and construction,"},{"time":746000,"text":"and I could go on and on. And this is to illustrate to you that"},{"time":751000,"text":"once you get the macro-economy straightened out,"},{"time":753000,"text":"the opportunities in various other sectors are enormous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758000,"text":"We have opportunities in agriculture, like I said."},{"time":761000,"text":"We have opportunities in solid minerals. We have a lot of minerals"},{"time":765000,"text":"that no one has even invested in or explored. And we realized"},{"time":768000,"text":"that without the proper legislation to make that possible,"},{"time":771000,"text":"that wouldn't happen. So we've now got a mining code"},{"time":774000,"text":"that is comparable with some of the best in the world."},{"time":778000,"text":"We have opportunities in housing and real estate."},{"time":780000,"text":"There was nothing in a country of 140 million people --"},{"time":784000,"text":"no shopping malls as you know them here."},{"time":790000,"text":"This was an investment opportunity for someone"},{"time":793000,"text":"that excited the imagination of people."},{"time":796000,"text":"And now, we have a situation in which the businesses in this mall"},{"time":799000,"text":"are doing four times the turnover that they had projected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"So, huge things in construction, real estate,"},{"time":806000,"text":"mortgage markets. Financial services:"},{"time":809000,"text":"we had 89 banks. Too many not doing their real business."},{"time":813000,"text":"We consolidated them from 89 to 25 banks by requiring"},{"time":817000,"text":"that they increase their capital -- share capital."},{"time":822000,"text":"And it went from about 25 million dollars to 150 million dollars."},{"time":827000,"text":"The banks -- these banks are now consolidated, and that strengthening"},{"time":831000,"text":"of the banking system has attracted a lot of investment from outside."},{"time":835000,"text":"Barclays Bank of the U.K. is bringing in 500 million."},{"time":839000,"text":"Standard Chartered has brought in 140 million."},{"time":843000,"text":"And I can go on. Dollars, on and on, into the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846000,"text":"We are doing the same with the insurance sector."},{"time":848000,"text":"So in financial services, a great deal of opportunity."},{"time":851000,"text":"In tourism, in many African countries, a great opportunity."},{"time":857000,"text":"And that's what many people know East Africa for:"},{"time":861000,"text":"the wildlife, the elephants, and so on."},{"time":864000,"text":"But managing the tourism market in a way"},{"time":866000,"text":"that can really benefit the people is very important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"So what am I trying to say? I'm trying to tell you"},{"time":873000,"text":"that there's a new wave on the continent."},{"time":876000,"text":"A new wave of openness and democratization in which, since 2000,"},{"time":881000,"text":"more than two-thirds of African countries have had"},{"time":883000,"text":"multi-party democratic elections."},{"time":886000,"text":"Not all of them have been perfect, or will be,"},{"time":889000,"text":"but the trend is very clear."},{"time":891000,"text":"I'm trying to tell you that since the past three years,"},{"time":895000,"text":"the average rate of growth on the continent has moved"},{"time":898000,"text":"from about 2.5 percent to about five percent per annum."},{"time":902000,"text":"This is better than the performance of many OECD countries."},{"time":907000,"text":"So it's clear that things are changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":911000,"text":"Conflicts are down on the continent;"},{"time":914000,"text":"from about 12 conflicts a decade ago,"},{"time":916000,"text":"we are down to three or four conflicts --"},{"time":918000,"text":"one of the most terrible, of course, of which is Darfur."},{"time":921000,"text":"And, you know, you have the neighborhood effect where"},{"time":924000,"text":"if something is going on in one part of the continent,"},{"time":926000,"text":"it looks like the entire continent is affected."},{"time":929000,"text":"But you should know that this continent is not --"},{"time":932000,"text":"is a continent of many countries, not one country."},{"time":938000,"text":"And if we are down to three or four conflicts,"},{"time":940000,"text":"it means that there are plenty of opportunities to invest"},{"time":943000,"text":"in stable, growing, exciting economies"},{"time":950000,"text":"where there's plenty of opportunity."},{"time":954000,"text":"And I want to just make one point about this investment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"The best way to help Africans today"},{"time":962000,"text":"is to help them to stand on their own feet."},{"time":965000,"text":"And the best way to do that is by helping create jobs."},{"time":970000,"text":"There's no issue with fighting malaria and putting money in that"},{"time":974000,"text":"and saving children's lives. That's not what I'm saying. That is fine."},{"time":979000,"text":"But imagine the impact on a family: if the parents can be employed"},{"time":983000,"text":"and make sure that their children go to school,"},{"time":985000,"text":"that they can buy the drugs to fight the disease themselves."},{"time":988000,"text":"If we can invest in places where you yourselves make money"},{"time":992000,"text":"whilst creating jobs and helping people stand on their own feet,"},{"time":997000,"text":"isn't that a wonderful opportunity? Isn't that the way to go?"},{"time":1002000,"text":"And I want to say that some of the best people to invest in"},{"time":1005000,"text":"on the continent are the women."},{"time":1008000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1015000,"text":"I have a CD here. I'm sorry that I didn't say anything on time."},{"time":1020000,"text":"Otherwise, I would have liked you to have seen this."},{"time":1022000,"text":"It says, \"Africa: Open for Business.\""},{"time":1026000,"text":"And this is a video that has actually won an award"},{"time":1029000,"text":"as the best documentary of the year."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Understand that the woman who made it"},{"time":1033000,"text":"is going to be in Tanzania, where they're having the session in June."},{"time":1039000,"text":"But it shows you Africans, and particularly African women, who"},{"time":1044000,"text":"against all odds have developed businesses, some of them world-class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049000,"text":"One of the women in this video, Adenike Ogunlesi,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"making children's clothes --"},{"time":1054000,"text":"which she started as a hobby and grew into a business."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Mixing African materials, such as we have,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"with materials from elsewhere."},{"time":1064000,"text":"So, she'll make a little pair of dungarees with corduroys,"},{"time":1069000,"text":"with African material mixed in. Very creative designs,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"has reached a stage where she even had an order from Wal-Mart."},{"time":1079000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1081000,"text":"For 10,000 pieces."},{"time":1084000,"text":"So that shows you that we have people who are capable of doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1088000,"text":"And the women are diligent. They are focused; they work hard."},{"time":1093000,"text":"I could go on giving examples:"},{"time":1095000,"text":"Beatrice Gakuba of Rwanda, who opened up a flower business"},{"time":1099000,"text":"and is now exporting to the Dutch auction in Amsterdam each morning"},{"time":1104000,"text":"and is employing 200 other women and men to work with her."},{"time":1109000,"text":"However, many of these are starved for capital to expand,"},{"time":1114000,"text":"because nobody believes outside of our countries"},{"time":1117000,"text":"that we can do what is necessary. Nobody thinks in terms of a market."},{"time":1122000,"text":"Nobody thinks there's opportunity."},{"time":1125000,"text":"But I'm standing here saying that those who miss the boat now,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"will miss it forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"So if you want to be in Africa, think about investing."},{"time":1137000,"text":"Think about the Beatrices, think about the Adenikes of this world,"},{"time":1143000,"text":"who are doing incredible things, that are bringing them"},{"time":1146000,"text":"into the global economy, whilst at the same time making sure"},{"time":1149000,"text":"that their fellow men and women are employed,"},{"time":1152000,"text":"and that the children in those households get educated"},{"time":1154000,"text":"because their parents are earning adequate income."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1158000,"text":"So I invite you to explore the opportunities."},{"time":1163000,"text":"When you go to Tanzania, listen carefully,"},{"time":1167000,"text":"because I'm sure you will hear of the various openings that there will be"},{"time":1171000,"text":"for you to get involved in something that will do good"},{"time":1176000,"text":"for the continent, for the people and for yourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1181000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1182000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}